      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BEES HIVE (1) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth (30.17) in a Grade 5 at Wentworth Park. Solid record here winning three races. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Better than last start and worth following up. LATEST TWIST (8) showed blistering pace early and gave a sight when in the minors, beaten 4 lengths over 515m this track in 29.76. Won at his only start from this draw. Leading player again. SAMMY'S BEACH (2) finds it hard to break through. Finished in the minors last time when second (30.86) at Gunnedah making it back to back placings. Has performed well from this box with a win and seven minor placings to her name from 12 starts. Bold showing expected. SMART STYLE (4) defied the market to win last start and can go on with it.",
